[Desktop Entry]
Type=Application
Version=1.0
Name=Install Corvid OS
GenericName=System Installer
Comment=Install Corvid OS to disk (LUKS full-disk encryption by default)
Exec=pkexec calamares
TryExec=calamares
Icon=corvid
Terminal=false
StartupNotify=true
Categories=Qt;System;Settings;
Keywords=install;installer;calamares;disk;
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Desktop-icon TRUST note (KDE Plasma):
# Plasma will NOT run a .desktop launcher dropped on the Desktop until the file
# is either (a) marked executable (chmod +x) AND owned/trusted, or (b) flagged
# trusted via KDE's KAuthorized/"trusted" metadata. On first double-click of an
# un-trusted launcher Plasma shows the "Untrusted application launcher" dialog
# instead of running it. This file being in /etc/skel means every new user gets
# a copy in ~/Desktop, but skel copies preserve 0644 (not executable), so the
# trust prompt will appear until something marks it +x / trusted.
#
# This comment is informational only. The actual chmod/trust step belongs in
# 0600-branding.hook.chroot or a first-boot step, NOT here. Do not rely on
# this comment to grant trust.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
